OL,3,CParish council silences church bells
OL,4,Cafter complaint from angry villager
OL,6,FA parish council in Devon has paid
OL,7,Fmore than #2,000 to adjust the
OL,8,Fmechanism of its village church clock
OL,9,Ffollowing a singular noise complaint.
OL,11,FThe bells of St John the Baptist's
OL,12,FChurch, in Witheridge, had chimed
OL,13,Fthroughout the day and night, every
OL,14,Ffifteen minutes, for around 150 years.
OL,16,FHowever, they stopped in January,
OL,17,Fafter North East Devon Council served
OL,18,Fthe parish council with a noise
OL,19,Fabatement order, following a complaint
OL,20,Fabout the bells.
